</taxonomicName>
is related to both 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFD3FFD0FCB2A17B2D94AB2A" box="[848,963,1119,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vartalapa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayana">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFD3FFD0FCB2A17B2D94AB2A" box="[848,963,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">malayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFD3FFD0FC19A17B2A04AB2A" box="[1019,1107,1119,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vartalapa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFD3FFD0FC19A17B2A04AB2A" box="[1019,1107,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having paraphyses that are expanded with serrated margin caudally.
</paragraph>
